This paper is primarily focused on the performance analysis of mobile edge computing (MEC) networks, which are wireless networks that provide low-latency computing services using devices at the network edge. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper involves the interplay of theories of stochastic geometry, queueing, and parallel computing, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the tradeoffs between latency, network coverage, and network stability, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.PF (Performance).
